{
  "abstract": "In field trial conducted in a wilt-sick vertisol plot at lCRlSAT\r\nCentre during the 1987-88, 1988-89 and 1989-90 crop seasons, no\r\nDifferences In Fuserlum wilt Incidence were observed in a set of \r\nSusceptible, tolerant and resistant Pigeonpea cultivar between row and hlll \r\n Sown plot. Similarly, no change in wilt reaction war observed when\r\na susceptible and resistant cultivar were sown either pure or mixed on\r\nhills. HIII-rowing can be more economical for evaluating large numbers of\r\ngenotypes for wilt resistance than row-Sowing as only one fifth of the area\r\nis required and thus operational expenses are reduced,\r\n",
